Ad Text:
Our Why

Datacom works with organisations and communities across Australia and New Zealand to make a difference in people’s lives and help organisations use the power of tech to innovate and grow.

About the Role (your why)

Our Intelligent Workspace team is dedicated to transforming how our customers and support teams work by leveraging automation, intelligent tools, and modern workplace solutions. As a Senior Automation Specialist, you will play a pivotal role in designing, developing, and implementing automation solutions that streamline processes, improve efficiency, and enhance the user experience within our clients’ workplace environments both internal and external. You will be key in shaping the automation team by identifying opportunities, developing the processes, designing and implementing solutions, mentoring colleagues, and evaluating suitable tools to help drive innovation for the team and to deliver the best outcome for both internal and external customers.

Our office is based in Brisbane CBD. We believe in bringing people together in person when it matters, but also value the flexibility of remote work for a healthy work/life balance. You and your team decide what works best!

We’re seeking a self-motivated professional who takes pride in producing high-quality work, demonstrates exceptional attention to detail, and embraces a mindset of continuous improvement. You’ll find satisfaction in making a meaningful impact while consistently delivering productive, results-driven outcomes.

** Please note that due to customer requirements, this role requires Australian Citizenship and eligibility to undertake a Federal Government Security Clearances ** 

What you’ll do

Lead the design and delivery of automation solutions that revolutionise workplace processes and streamline IT service delivery
Collaborate with internal and external customers to uncover opportunities for efficiency and innovation—including integration with AI models and large language models (LLMs).
Develop advanced scripts, integrations, and automation workflows using the latest cloud platforms and automation tools.
Mentor and inspire colleagues, sharing your expertise to elevate our Intelligent Workspace solutions.
Drive alignment across technical teams to ensure automation projects support our broader workplace strategy.
Champion best practices and provide technical guidance and training on automation tools and processes.

We’re agile and responsive to changing needs—your role will evolve as technology and customer requirements do.

What you’ll bring

Required Experience:

Proven experience designing and implementing process automation solutions within a workplace or IT environment.
Strong capabilities with automation tools and scripting languages (e.g., PowerShell, Python, RPA platforms).
Experience integrating systems and workflows within Microsoft 365 or comparable enterprise environments.
Ability to work collaboratively with technical and non-technical stakeholders to deliver automation projects.
Proven experience in driving continuous improvement initiatives, with a track record of identifying and implementing enhancements to workflows, systems, or processes. Demonstrates precision and thoroughness in execution, ensuring high-quality outcomes through strong attention to detail.

Desired Experience:

Familiarity with Modern Work concepts, including modern device management, digital collaboration tools, and end-user computing.
Experience with Azure infrastructure and services including Logic Apps, Log Analytics and Azure Key Vault.
Hands-on experience with Azure DevOps, including the design, implementation, and maintenance of CI/CD pipelines and code repositories, ensuring efficient, secure, and scalable software delivery practices.
Knowledge of ServiceNow, ITSM tools, or workflow automation platforms.
Industry certifications relevant to automation and/or modern workplace solutions.

Why join us here at Datacom?

Datacom is one of Australia and New Zealand’s largest suppliers of Information Technology professional services. We have managed to maintain a dynamic, agile, small business feel that is often diluted in larger organisations of our size. It's our people that give Datacom its unique culture and energy that you can feel from the moment you meet with us.

We care about our people and provide a range of perks such as social events, chill-out spaces, remote working, flexi-hours and professional development courses to name a few. You’ll have the opportunity to learn, develop your career, connect and bring your true self to work. You will be recognised and valued for your contributions and be able to do your work in a collegial, flat-structured environment.

We operate at the forefront of technology to help Australia and New Zealand’s largest enterprise organisations explore possibilities and solve their greatest challenges, so you will never run out of interesting new challenges and opportunities.

We want Datacom to be an inclusive and welcoming workplace for everyone and take pride in the steps we have taken and continue to take to make our environment fun and friendly, and our people feel supported.

Responsibilities
Support critical data engineering and business intelligence initiatives to drive strategic decisions and product development.
Deliver scalable analytical services to enhance client outcomes and provide key insights for portfolio management.
Join a team where your expertise is indispensable and highly valued.

Data Engineer - Commercial Risk Analytics

An exciting opportunity has become available for a passionate and innovative professional to join our dynamic Commercial Risk Analytics Team. In this role, you will be transforming data into actionable insights that drive business success, while ensuring the detailed integration of cutting-edge technology and strategic analytics.

This is a hybrid role with the flexibility to work both virtually and from our Aon offices.

Aon is in the business of better decisions

At Aon, we shape decisions for the better to protect and enrich the lives of people around the world.

As an organization, we are united through trust as one inclusive, diverse team, and we are passionate about helping our colleagues and clients succeed.

What the day will look like

Data Assets Design: Develop and enhance data assets tailored to business needs, supporting analytics and intelligence projects.
Automated Pipelines: Create and lead automated data ingestion pipelines using Databricks with AWS S3, and SSIS with Microsoft Azure.
Data Quality: Implement routines for data cleaning and standardization, using Python in Databricks notebooks for quality assurance.
SQL Development: Craft SQL scripts for data views, optimizing data flows to introduce new report dimensions and metrics.
Deployment & Monitoring: Deploy notebooks and scripts in production, configure cloud auto-scaling, and supervise performance. Integrate API solutions for GenAI module triggers.
Troubleshooting: Address data ingestion and processing issues, ensuring smooth report generation in PowerBI.
Collaboration: Work closely with data scientists, domain experts, and commercial risk leaders to build data infrastructure to support a broad variety of client risk analytics and business intelligence projects.
Technical Translation: Convert business requirements into technical specifications.

How this opportunity is different

As an Aon colleague, you will never be limited by your job title. Instead, you will learn and grow alongside some of the most versatile individuals in the business, who genuinely want you to be the best version of yourself.

We honestly believe that our culture is different, with authentic and inquisitive individuals who each bring something unique to our team.

Skills and experience that will lead to success

This role seeks for a forward-thinking Data Engineer to support our growing Commercial Risk Analytics team. Additionally, you will have the following:

5+ years of experience in data engineering, analytics, or business intelligence
Proficiency in SQL, Python, and cloud-based ETL tools like SSIS or Alteryx
Hands-on experience with Databricks (or similar platforms)
Knowledge of data architectures (data warehouses, lakehouse, and data mesh)
Skilled in Power BI for visualization and dashboard troubleshooting
Ability to document workflows, conduct testing, and ensure data quality
Experience integrating APIs and GenAI modules is a plus
Bachelor’s degree or equivalent experience in Computer Science, IT, Engineering, or a related field (Master’s a plus)

Preferred

Databricks certification
Exposure to MLOps and Natural Language Processing (NLP)

 

How we support our colleagues

In addition to our comprehensive benefits package, we encourage a diverse workforce. Plus, our agile, inclusive environment allows you to manage your wellbeing and work/life balance, ensuring you can be your best self at Aon. Furthermore, all colleagues enjoy two “Global Wellbeing Days” each year, encouraging you to take time to focus on yourself. We offer a variety of working style solutions, but we also recognise that flexibility goes beyond just the place of work... and we are all for it. We call this Smart Working!

Our continuous learning culture inspires and equips you to learn, share and grow, helping you achieve your fullest potential. As a result, at Aon, you are more connected, more relevant, and more valued.

We provide individuals with disabilities reasonable accommodations to participate in the job application or interview process, to perform essential job functions, and to receive other benefits and privileges of employment in accordance with applicable law. Please contact us to request an accommodation on ReasonableAdjustments@Aon.com

Aon values an innovative, diverse workplace where all colleagues feel empowered to be their authentic selves. Aon is proud to be an equal opportunity workplace.

IVR Developer - Conversational AI Specialist (Contract)

Leading Telco client (consulting through FinXL)

FinXL Professional Services is a leading IT consultancy that partners with clients to bridge the gap between business needs and technology capabilities. Since 2003, we've been delivering high-value ICT services across government, finance, telecommunications, and enterprise sectors.

FinXL is seeking an IVR Developer - Conversational AI Specialist (Contract) to join our consulting team and be deployed with a leading Telco client on a key transformation engagement.

"Must be an Australian Citizen"

Responsibilities

Design, develop, and deploy robust IVR systems with intuitive, human-centered Voice User Interface (VUI) capabilities.

Implement solutions for Voice Biometrics and build intent tags to ensure accurate, customer-driven interactions.

Implement end-to-end call flows, including deep API integration and robust reporting principles.

Produce technical design documentation and contribute to the execution of test cases for IVR development.

Key Skills & Experience

Strong understanding and proven experience in NLU interaction design and implementation.

Experience in Voice Biometrics application design and implementation.

Proficiency in IVR development and Customer Experience (CX) methodologies.

Experience with Text-to-Speech (TTS) and IVR application testing.

Detailed knowledge of the full software engineering life cycle (planning, scoping, development, and handover).

Ability to communicate effectively with both business stakeholders and engineering teams.

Familiarity with major Contact Centre environments (e.g., Genesys, Cisco, Nuance, NICE).

Why Join FinXL?

Lead advanced Conversational AI and NLU initiatives.

Work on a high-profile, complex government transformation project.

Long-term contract with a leading client through FinXL.

Next Steps If you would like to apply for this opportunity, please submit your CV via SEEK. Please note that due to the volume of responses, only shortlisted consultants will be contacted.

Full-stack AI Developer

Hybrid – Sydney, NSW, Australia
Full-time

Build the Next Generation of AI-Driven Workflows

Our client is an early-stage startup on a mission to redefine how teams work by using AI to simplify complexity, automate the manual, and surface the insights that truly matter.

Modern professionals spend far too much time on repetitive admin, disconnected tools, and fragmented data. Our client is building an intelligent system that changes that - combining automation, memory, and context-awareness to help people focus on the work that drives impact.

The Role

Our client is looking for a Fullstack AI Developer to help us design, build, and scale our next-generation platform — an AI-powered workspace that learns, assists, and evolves with its users.

This isn’t a typical developer role. You’ll be joining a small, ambitious founding team where your ideas, code, and technical decisions will shape the product from day one.

What You’ll Do

Design and build AI-powered features using modern frameworks and cloud-native technologies

Create responsive, intuitive user experiences that feel effortless

Collaborate closely with product and data teams to bring AI models into production

Own projects end-to-end - from concept to deployment and optimisation

Write clean, efficient, well-documented code that scales

Contribute to technical discussions and continuously improve performance and reliability

What You’ll Bring

2+ years of experience in full-stack development

Proficiency in React and Node.js

Strong understanding of JavaScript/TypeScript

Experience integrating or working with AI/ML models

Familiarity with RESTful APIs and microservices architecture

Cloud experience with AWS, GCP, or Azure

A problem-solving mindset, ownership mentality, and strong communication skills




If this sounds like you, we’d love to hear from you.


Please note that only candidates who meet the above criteria and hold full working rights in Australia will be contacted.
